                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="layout__column1-2 col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-5 offset-lg-1">
                            <div class="text-module">
                                <h3>Nigeria</h3>
                                <p>Due in large part to the lack of adequate learning materials and resources, many
                                    Nigerian university students are unaware of global issues and development
                                    initiatives happening around the world. Students are thus disadvantaged and not
                                    fitted to meet national and international challenges that may well have been fully
                                    addressed in academic literature.
                                    There are so many issues of importance and so many students hungry for the
                                    challenge, but they are currently being starved of the necessary tools to meet those
                                    challenges. Even from a very foundational level of understanding the issues at hand
                                    let alone the solutions, mean students need to be fed through the medium of
                                    literature.</p>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                <p>
                                    Due to lack of education through a scarcity of books many are unaware of such core
                                    issues as - the reason for the transition from the Millennium Development Goals to
                                    the Sustainable Development Goals, international trade, issues of migration and
                                    forced displacement of people, climate change, humanitarian aid, foreign and
                                    development aid, globalisation and inequality and many more. </p>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                <p>Vickies Foundation will donate development books to Universities across Nigeria and
                                    provide e-books in the long run. We will also sensitise the students and general
                                    public to the benefits that come with global awareness.</p>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                <p>Our other focus area is for students who do not have a clear career path, some lack
                                    basic employability skills, others do not have the leadership experience needed in
                                    the University or workplace. Being a leader does not necessarily mean someone at the
                                    fore-front always, but it is important for everyone to be able to coordinate teams,
                                    small groups and use their voice when required. Hence, Vickies Foundation will
                                    organise self-development seminars and workshops to groom the students and youths on
                                    their path to greatness.</p>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                <p>We have the interest of orphans, school-dropouts, disabled and the marginalised at
                                    heart, hence, we would organise free vocational skills training to equip them with
                                    certain skills they can use to earn some income and sustain their livelihood.
                                </p>
                                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                                <p>Vickies Foundation is concerned about the homeless as well and so we plan to make
                                    some basic needs donations to help these individuals live another happy day.</p>

