                                <h3>Objectives</h3>
                                <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>To contribute to community developmental works in Nigeria in the form of
                                        enhancing education by providing libraries, books and materials for deprived
                                        schools. </li>
                                    <li>Empower youths and students by organising seminars in areas of leadership,
                                        volunteering, entrepreneurship, mental health and inciting community
                                        responsibility in them. Organise free tutorial classes for students from Junior
                                        through to Senior WAEC. </li>
                                    <li>Promote women empowerment by empowering girls in sciences and entrepreneurship
                                        in young females. </li>
                                    <li>Support graduates who want to study abroad by providing them with scholarship
                                        information and guiding them through the scholarship application process. </li>
                                    <li>Empowering school dropouts and marginalised youths by providing free vocational
                                        skills workshop relevant for their sustainable living. </li>
                                    <li>Make charitable donations to the orphans and homeless and enhance livelihoods by
                                        providing shelter and casual jobs for the homeless. </li>

                                </ul>
                                </p>

